Verb[edit]

iaceam

  1. first-person singular present active subjunctive of iaceō
    1. "may I lie prostrate, may I lie down; may I recline"
    2. "may I lie ill, may I be sick"
    3. "may I linger, may I tarry"
    4. "may I be placed or situated, may I lie"
    5. "may I be low, flat or level"
    6. "may I lie still"
    7. "may I lie dead"
    8. "may I lie in ruins"
    9. "may I hang down loose"
    10. (of the face or eyes) "may I be fixed on the ground, may I be cast down"
    11. "may I be indolent, idle or inactive"
    12. "may I lie dormant or abandoned, may I be of no avail"
    13. "may I lie overthrown; may I be refuted; may I be despised"
    14. (of speech or language) "may I be languid, dull or lifeless"
